       @{fg shine} ___________________________________________________________@{fg text}
       @{fg shine}|@{fg text}                                                           |
       @{fg shine}|@{fg text}            @{fg shine}@{b}Preferences@{ub}@{fg text} for @{b}FileTypeInfo@{ub}.dopus5            |
       @{fg shine}|@{fg text}                            V 1.1 (09.09.1999)             |
       @{fg shine}|@{fg text}___________________________________________________________|



              @{" FileTypeInfo.prefs " rx "/ARexx/Check SYS:Prefs/FileTypeInfo.prefs 1.0"}

              is a preferences-program for FileTypeInfo.
              It should be found in SYS:Prefs/
              Click on the button above to test this.

              If this test was sucessful,
              you can start the prefsprogram
              by using FileTypeInfo`s menue.

              By using the following button
              you can start the prefsprogram from here:

              @{" FileTypeInfo.prefs " rx " /Prefs/FileTypeInfo.prefs"}



       ___________________________________________________________________@{fg shine}
       -------------------------------------------------------------------@{fg text}

       If you have just installed or updated FileTypeInfo.dopus5
       on its startup the here described preferencesprogram will appear
       and write a prefs-file to ENV: and ENVARC:
       Simply quit it using 'Cancel'.

       ___________________________________________________________________@{fg shine}
       -------------------------------------------------------------------@{fg text}


       @{"" ""}@{bg shine}  GUI elements  @{bg back}@{"" ""}



       @{fg shine}@{b}FileTypeUtils@{ub}@{fg text} (string-gadget)

         Default: DOpus5:Tools/FileTypeUtils/

         The directory,
         where the FileTypeUtils-stuff can be found,
         e.g.the Guides.


       @{fg shine}@{b}FileTypes@{ub}@{fg text} (string-gadget)

         Default: DOpus5:Filetypes/

         This is the Directory
         where DOpus finds its filetypes.

         If you change this here,
         it wouldn`t affect DOpus,
         but the list-programs will show the contents
         of a different filetypes-directory.

         Do only change this path for experimntal purposes,
         and only, if you exacly know, what you do !
         Afterwards do not use the 'Save'-button, but click at 'Use'.


       @{fg shine}@{b}FileType-storage@{ub}@{fg text} (string-gadget)

         Default: DOpus5:Storage/Filetypes/

         See above.

         This is the directory,
         where the filetypemanager
         stores filetypes.

         If you change this here,
         the Storagelist-Button
         will show the contents
         of a different filetypes-directory.

         Do only change this path for experimntal purposes,
         and only, if you exacly know, what you do !
         Afterwards do not use the 'Save'-button, but click at 'Use'.

       @{fg shine}@{b}___________________________________________________________________@{ub}@{fg text}
       ŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻ

       @{fg shine}@{b}FileTypeInfo.prefs@{ub}@{fg text} (string-gadget)

         Default: SYS:Prefs/

         In this directory
         FileTypeInfo.dopus5 finds
         its preferences program.


       @{fg shine}@{b}GetType (GT)@{ub}@{fg text} (string-gadget)

         Default: SYS:C/

         In this directory
         FileTypeInfo.dopus5 looks for
         the program GT.


       @{fg shine}@{b}IFFMaster@{ub}@{fg text} (string-gadget)

         Default: SYS:SystemIFFMaster/

         In this directory
         FileTypeInfo.dopus5 looks for
         the IFFMaster.

       @{fg shine}@{b}Triton@{ub}@{fg text} (string-gadget)

         Default: SYS:Prefs/

         In this directory
         FileTypeInfo.prefs finds
         the Triton preferencesprogram.

       @{fg shine}@{b}___________________________________________________________________@{ub}@{fg text}
       ŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻ

       @{b}Shadow@{ub} (Check-box)

         Default: On

         Shade those buttons which are not usable,
         e.g.if the IFFMaster can`t be found.


       @{b}Safety-check@{ub} (Check-box)

         Default: On

         Check on startup if all needed fils can be found,
         by running FileTypeInfo.check.
         If everything is o.k.
         this only happens once after booting.

         If you switch this item off,
         FTI will never check,
         if all needed programs and libraries
         are on their right place.
         

       @{b}Errorlevel@{ub} (Cycle-gadget)

         Default: 1

         Complains each missed program on startup.
         If you set it to 2,
         FileTypeInfo.check will only carp
         if necessary libraries can`t be found.

         All problems and @{b}Error-Codes@{ub} you can see @{" here " link "FileTypeInfo.Guide/Codes"}


       @{b}Stack@{ub} (Cycle-gadget)

         Default: 8192

         A lower stack could cause problems.
         I think it was the IFFMaster.

       @{fg shine}@{b}___________________________________________________________________@{ub}@{fg text}
       ŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻ

       @{" Snapshot " rx "/ARexx/SystemReq The button:*n*n- Snapshot -"}

         This permanently saves the current dimension
         and position of the program-window.

         If you didn't start the prefs program
         from FileTypeInfo`s menue,
         you`ll be told to run FileTypeInfo.

         ATTENTION:
         If you do not do this, and if you click on 'continue',
         the prefs-window seems to be frozen,
         but it is just waiting for you to start FileTypeInfo.
         Simply do it ;-)


         If you start the prefs program from within
         FileTypeInfo, please position the program`s
         windows *before* choosing this function in
         order to permanently snapshot it.

         To unsnapshot the window, simply delete the
         files
         @{" ENVARC:Triton/ " rx "/ARexx/Lister ENVARC:Triton FileTypeInfo.win.1 FileTypeInfo.win.2 FileTypeInfo.win.3 SOURCE"} FileTypeInfo.win.1
         and FileTypeInfo.win.2 and FileTypeInfo.win.3
         This directory is created in ENV: as well as
         in ENVARC: the very first time any triton
         program is quit.
         The particular file in question is created
         in ENV: when you quit the program for the
         very first time and will be copied to ENVARC:
         when you use the snapshot function.

         You can, by the way, snapshot any application
         using Triton.library (including all FileTypeUtils)
         by using the @{" Triton " SYSTEM "SYS:Prefs/Triton"} prefs program.
         To do this, start the application and than
         start Triton-Prefs, where you should mark
         the program to be snapshot and then take a
         look at the "Windows" division.


       @{" Fonts " SYSTEM "SYS:Prefs/Font"}

         This gadget will run the Workbench`s
         font preferences program.

         '@{fg shine}@{b}Default Text setting ...@{ub}@{fg text}'
         determines the font used for the @{b}gadgets@{ub}
         and the @{b}window texts@{ub},
         thus taking influence on the @{b}width of the main window@{ub}


       @{" Triton " SYSTEM "SYS:Prefs/Triton"}

         The Triton prefs program offers some further
         preferences options.




       _____________________________________________________________@{fg shine}
       -------------------------------------------------------------@{fg text}

       @{"" ""}@{bg shine}  Menu functions  @{bg back}@{"" ""}


       @{b}Help@{ub}

         switches the help text on/off.

         Note 1:
         Choosing this menu option will save
         all current preferences after checking
         their validity, including of course
         the status of this menu option.

       @{b}Guide@{ub}

         displays this guide

       @{fg shine}@{b}____________________________________________@{ub}@{fg text}
       ŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻ

       @{b}Load previous@{ub}

         Loads the settings which have been set
         with "Use" or "Save" earlier.

       @{b}Load default@{ub}

         Loads the default settings

       @{b}Load again@{ub}

         Reloads the settings
         In case you hit the wrong keys :-)

       @{fg shine}@{b}____________________________________________@{ub}@{fg text}
       ŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻ

       @{b}Save Use Cancel@{ub}

         Does exactly the same as the gadgets
         at the bottom of the prefs-window.

         Please note that before
         the program quits, the settings
         will be validated.
         Thus the delay ;-)
         If an error occurs,
         a requester will appear,
         the window will stay open
         and no settings will be saved.
         The settings also won't be saved
         if no settings have been changed.

       _____________________________________________________________@{fg shine}
